{% comment %}
  Universal condition care page. Drives /pages/fungal-acne,
  /pages/seb-derm-dandruff, and /pages/tinea-versicolor from a single
  section file. All condition-specific copy is set in the case block
  at the top; the rest of the section uses those variables.

  Structure (Nurx-inspired but care-focused):
    1. Hero
    2. Trust bar
    3. What it is (plain-language explainer)
    4. Symptoms checklist
    5. How Kyn Skyn treats it
    6. What's included
    7. The process (4 steps)
    8. Pricing summary (links to full pricing on consultation page)
    9. Condition-specific FAQ
    10. Final CTA
{% endcomment %}

{%- case page.handle -%}
  {%- when 'fungal-acne' -%}
    {%- assign condition_name = 'Fungal Acne' -%}
    {%- assign condition_subtitle = "Malassezia folliculitis. The acne that isn't acne." -%}
    {%- assign hero_heading = 'Fungal acne, finally diagnosed and treated.' -%}
    {%- assign hero_sub = "It's yeast, not bacteria. Which is why your acne products aren't working. A Kyn Skyn provider gets you the right diagnosis and a treatment plan built for the actual cause." -%}
    {%- assign condition_slug = 'fungal-acne' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_heading = 'A yeast condition that looks like acne' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p1 = '<em>Malassezia folliculitis</em> is an inflammatory infection of the hair follicle caused by <em>Malassezia</em>, a yeast that lives on nearly all human skin. When the local environment shifts, the yeast can overgrow inside the follicle and trigger an immune response. The result is a cluster of small, often itchy bumps people mistake for acne.' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p2 = 'Standard acne treatments do not target yeast and often make fungal acne worse. Many of them also contain ingredients <em>Malassezia</em> feeds on. Years of misdiagnosis is the rule, not the exception.' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p3 = "The fix is straightforward once it's named: an antifungal that actually targets <em>Malassezia</em>, paired with a routine that doesn't feed it." -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_heading = 'Signs you might have fungal acne' -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_csv = 'Uniform small bumps that look almost identical|Itchiness, especially after sweating|Breakouts on the forehead, hairline, jawline, chest, or upper back|Acne treatments (benzoyl peroxide, antibiotics) made it worse|Flares with heat, humidity, or after antibiotic courses' -%}
    {%- assign treatment_heading = 'How we treat fungal acne' -%}
    {%- assign treatment_p1 = 'Your provider reviews your photos and intake, confirms the diagnosis, and prescribes a topical antifungal (e.g., ketoconazole) where needed. From there, the treatment plan covers the routine that keeps the yeast in check long-term, not just clearing the current flare.' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan = 'quarterly' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan_label = 'Quarterly Treatment Plan' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_reason = 'Fungal acne almost always relapses without an ongoing routine. Most people stay clear with the Quarterly Plan, which covers the maintenance phase.' -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_heading = 'Ready to actually treat it?' -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_sub = 'Submit your intake, get a written diagnosis from a licensed clinician, and start a treatment plan that targets the actual cause.' -%}

  {%- when 'seb-derm-dandruff' -%}
    {%- assign condition_name = 'Seb Derm & Dandruff' -%}
    {%- assign condition_subtitle = 'Seborrheic dermatitis and dandruff. Same cause, same fix.' -%}
    {%- assign hero_heading = 'Stop the flaking, redness, and itch.' -%}
    {%- assign hero_sub = 'Seborrheic dermatitis and dandruff both come from <em>Malassezia</em> overgrowth where your skin is oiliest. The right treatment can clear it in weeks and keep it clear with a simple maintenance routine.' -%}
    {%- assign condition_slug = 'seb-derm-dandruff' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_heading = 'Inflammation triggered by yeast in oily skin' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p1 = 'Seborrheic dermatitis is a chronic inflammatory condition driven by <em>Malassezia</em>, the same yeast behind fungal acne and dandruff. It typically shows up where your skin produces the most oil: scalp, around the nose, eyebrows, behind the ears, and the upper chest.' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p2 = 'Dandruff is essentially scalp seb derm with less inflammation. They sit on the same spectrum, respond to the same treatment, and the line between them is fuzzy.' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p3 = "Most people have been told it's &ldquo;just dry skin&rdquo; and given a moisturizer that makes it worse. The actual fix is an antifungal active that brings the yeast back into balance, then a maintenance routine that holds." -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_heading = 'Signs you might have seb derm or dandruff' -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_csv = 'Flaky or scaly patches on scalp, eyebrows, sides of nose, or chest|Redness that comes and goes, often with itch|Greasy or powdery scale, sometimes mistaken for dryness|Itchy scalp with persistent flakes that anti-dandruff shampoo barely touches|Worse with stress, weather changes, or certain hair products' -%}
    {%- assign treatment_heading = 'How we treat seb derm and dandruff' -%}
    {%- assign treatment_p1 = 'Your provider reviews your photos and intake, confirms the diagnosis, and prescribes a topical antifungal (e.g., ketoconazole) for the affected zones. The treatment plan also includes the maintenance schedule, scalp and skin care choices, and what to do when triggers hit.' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan = 'quarterly' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan_label = 'Quarterly Treatment Plan' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_reason = "Seb derm and dandruff are chronic. The Quarterly Plan covers ongoing care so you're not starting over every flare." -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_heading = 'Get out of the flake-and-flare loop.' -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_sub = 'Submit your intake, get a written diagnosis, and start a treatment plan that holds.' -%}

  {%- when 'tinea-versicolor' -%}
    {%- assign condition_name = 'Tinea Versicolor' -%}
    {%- assign condition_subtitle = 'Discolored patches caused by Malassezia overgrowth.' -%}
    {%- assign hero_heading = 'Even out the patches.' -%}
    {%- assign hero_sub = "Light or dark spots on your chest, back, or shoulders are a yeast condition with a clear path to treatment. We'll get you sorted." -%}
    {%- assign condition_slug = 'tinea-versicolor' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_heading = "Yeast that disrupts the skin's pigment production" -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p1 = 'Tinea versicolor is caused by <em>Malassezia</em> overgrowing on the skin and producing compounds that interfere with melanin production in the affected areas. The result is patches that are lighter or darker than your surrounding skin, often most visible after sun exposure.' -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p2 = "It's common, harmless to your overall health, and very treatable. Most cases respond to a short course of topical antifungal. The discoloration itself takes weeks to months to even out after the yeast is treated, since pigment production needs time to recover." -%}
    {%- assign whatitis_p3 = 'It tends to come back during hot, humid months. A maintenance routine cuts down the frequency.' -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_heading = 'Signs you might have tinea versicolor' -%}
    {%- assign symptoms_csv = "Light or dark patches on chest, back, shoulders, or upper arms|Patches that don't tan with the rest of your skin|Fine, powdery scale when scratched|More visible in summer or after sun exposure|Returning year after year, especially in heat or humidity" -%}
    {%- assign treatment_heading = 'How we treat tinea versicolor' -%}
    {%- assign treatment_p1 = 'Your provider reviews your photos and intake, confirms the diagnosis, and prescribes a topical antifungal (e.g., ketoconazole). Most cases clear with a 2 to 4 week course. The pigment evens out over the weeks following treatment.' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan = 'one-time' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_plan_label = 'One-time Consult' -%}
    {%- assign recommended_reason = 'A single consult and a topical antifungal is often enough. If you flare seasonally, the recurring plans cover prevention.' -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_heading = 'Clear the patches, keep them clear.' -%}
    {%- assign final_cta_sub = 'Submit your intake, get a written diagnosis, and start a short topical antifungal course.' -%}

{%- endcase -%}

{%- assign symptoms = symptoms_csv | split: '|' -%}

<style>
